<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Doctor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If you had to pick one - what one would you pick ? And Dont Say Both  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>CH - 400mana saved, but long cast time<BR>Great for post battle heals, and well timed in battle heals.<BR>Would need to use 5x per hour to have mana gain over legs.<P>Symbol - 320 mana saved<BR>Great for buffing full group up front. 6x315<BR>~1900 mana saved per hr.<P>I was leaning toward Legs - reason being it would be nice to get into a group and hit everyone with Symbol withour going lom, oom.<P>But after looking at the numbers I am changing my mind to the BP. I can defently see using it more then 5x per hr (or is this incorrect thinking). Could be a life saver if I am ever OOM. With (Fungi, Chloro and manastone) or (crack) can easily gain back the 1800 mana symbol cost.<P>Thanks ALL<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dalur - Veeshan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Not to mention the difference in the stats:<P>Donal's Leggings of Mourning - AC 26 Str +8, Sta +8, Wis +8, HP +30, Mana +3<P>Donals Chestplate of Mourning: AC 40+12 Agi, +12 Dex, +12 Wis, +80 Mana<P>Not too hard to decide there.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Dalur Stouthealer<BR>60th Dwarven High Priest<BR>Veeshan Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Doctor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yep, didn't seem for it to be a silly question.<P>I am just so addicted to Regen that I hate taking off the fungi tunic, exspecially with a mana stone. But I did come to the realization (60 sec ago) that the BP has to be the way to go. I could be FH, use MS to gain mana, use BP , use MS to gain mana, slap on Fungi for a quick recovery. <BR>I was locked into thinking that it had to be one or the other (BP or Fungi) wasn't considering switching them out. my bad...</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Smegal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Donals BP anyday.   I still use mine very often, even in combat situations.  If I really wanted to Naltron the entire group I would use Naltrons Mark, but most the time I use Aegolism.<P>Smegal BoneMender<BR>High Priest, guild Afterlife, Mith Marr server.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mirriana_00</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I dont know.  I think you may just not realize how long 30 seconds is.  Do many clerics out there use this thing in combat or during downtime?<P>I'd just be scared of being locked down for that long.  No secondary heals.  No gate.  No DA.  Nothing, for 30 seconds.<P>I can cast CelHeal and med it back up in 30 seconds for 700-900hps healed.  Just seems to be quite risky for a free CH in the same time.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Auelan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I use my donal's bp to heal whenever I'm getting lom...quite helpful, since you can use /sit to med while it's casting.<P>Auelan Lifebringer<BR>58th season Templar of Tunare<BR>Enshadowed<BR>Brell Serilis server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cali</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">From my point of view, if someone said they would give me one or the other, I would go with BP.<P>1)Doubtfull my guild will ever kill Trak.<BR>2)Drop rates on EM BP is insanely rare compared to legs (from what I have seen).<BR>3)AC! AC! AC!<BR>4)Effects, while totaly cool on some things, should NOT be the sole reason I put on an item like a BP vs. Legs.  (Have watched to many people whine that the 'armor buff' isnt as good as the real one.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/rolleyes.gif"> )<P>ps: How did clerics get *****ed over with the summon food / water spells on Velious armor?!  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/mad.gif"><P>------------------<BR><B>~Calimayrn Anam'Cara</B><BR>Vicar of Tunare<BR><B>~Calizana Rhinelander</B><BR>Floating Barbarian Champion<BR><A HREF="http://www.lostorder.com" TARGET=_blank>Lost Order of Akalabeth</A><BR>Veeshan</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dalain</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Mirriana_00:<BR>I dont know.  I think you may just not realize how long 30 seconds is.  Do many clerics out there use this thing in combat or during downtime?<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I used it all the time in combat.  After getting used to a 30 second cheal, 10 seconds seems DAMN fast. :P<P>Dalain<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aladain</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Cali:<BR><B>ps: How did clerics get *****ed over with the summon food / water spells on Velious armor?!    <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/mad.gif"></B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Lol I agree   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>I'll have to dig up where Absor said that Bard kunark armor effects of summon food and summon water were weak to being put on their armor because of its difficulty.<P>Do you think because they made it summon 4 of each, our armor is that much more justified since its 4 times harder than kunark armor?   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Aladain<P>P.S. the patch message associated with this change took the cake   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>"Changed the effects on the Singing Steel Boots and Greaves. After a fair amount of concern from players, we have removed the summon food and water effects from these items. They have been replaced with modified versions of Aria of the Eagles (boots) and Appalling Screech (greaves). "<p>[This message has been edited by Aladain (edited 06-12-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gello</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Donal legs are wonderful for multigroup situations.  Just today doing Ixiblat we didn't have enough clerics for all the groups.  /target, cast hero, click legs, click gloves.  Only 140 mana to fully buff a person to 10 less ac and 155 less hp than your groupmates with aegis/marzin.<P>But the CH on the bp is all around more useful, imho.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aldur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Donal legs effect becomes useless as soon as you hit level 58.<P>Now velious legs - they are a different matter.  Very very nice effect :></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Smegal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">There are a number of battles in SoV where the breastplate is very useful.  The best example is a dragon named Aaryonar, he guards the Halls of the Forbidden in Temple of Veeshan.   Now this dragon has an AE dot that sucks 500 hit points over 10 ticks, and sucks 500 mana a tick for 10 ticks.   Which means once the dot hits you, it will suck 5000 mana in 60 seconds.  Now most us clerics have around 3000 mana +/- 350, which means we are OOM in 36 seconds even if we don't cast a single spell.    You can't med back, since every tick you get +21 mana from medding and -500 from the dot.   This is where Donals Breastplate and Shissar Apothic Staff come in.   Despite its 30 second cast, I've managed to use it 7 times in one fight with this dragon.<P>The Donals Leg effect is nice, but the peridot cost will eat you alive.  If I'm gonna use a single target base symbol I use Marzin or Aegolism.  If Naltron will suffice then I use Naltron's Mark and save 52.5 pp.<P>Smegal BoneMender<BR>High Priest, guild Afterlife, server Mith Marr.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lyrial</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I use my Donal BP in combat on guildraids and small exp camps all the time. I have a macro made that lets me cast it, sit, and stand back up again right before it goes off.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>It is useful and sometimes lifesaving.<P><P>------------------<BR>Lyrial<BR>Level 59 Templar on Cazic Thule and officer of Cohort Chalybeius</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aldur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">How do you do macros for casting armour spells?  I asked a few people and could never figure out how.<P>I'd dearly love to have one for Aof buffing with gauntlets.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
